00:47:12,957 --> 00:47:13,278
Thank you.

855
00:47:13,558 --> 00:47:16,239
So history is a very big part of the franchise.

856
00:47:16,259 --> 00:47:18,119
So how do you decide which country

857
00:47:18,179 --> 00:47:20,460
or which kind of historic US you choose

858
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,821
to work on for each games?

859
00:47:21,921 --> 00:47:22,201
Thank you.

860
00:47:23,762 --> 00:47:28,023
So that's a very common question in the sense

861
00:47:28,063 --> 00:47:28,203
that.

862
00:47:29,368 --> 00:47:31,689
There is a lot of guessing, people

863
00:47:31,869 --> 00:47:34,410
trying to guess what's the next installment.

864
00:47:35,350 --> 00:47:37,891
It's always a discussion between the creative team,

865
00:47:38,171 --> 00:47:41,733
the developers, the marketing, the HQ.

866
00:47:41,993 --> 00:47:43,594
We need to come up with an agreement where

867
00:47:43,894 --> 00:47:47,575
the team feels empowered about the setting.

868
00:47:47,655 --> 00:47:49,776
That's something they really want to explore.

869
00:47:50,196 --> 00:47:52,577
At the same time, we need to secure that it

870
00:47:52,617 --> 00:47:54,738
had some marketing appeal.

871
00:47:55,238 --> 00:47:57,719
So there is no rule, I would say.

872
00:47:57,759 --> 00:47:58,820
So it's really a...

873
00:47:59,820 --> 00:48:01,540
Which time period are you interested in?

874
00:48:01,680 --> 00:48:04,301
Does it make sense from a business point of perspective?

875
00:48:04,821 --> 00:48:05,941
Is the audience ready for that?

876
00:48:06,021 --> 00:48:06,502
Yes, okay.

877
00:48:07,442 --> 00:48:08,162
It's as simple.

878
00:48:08,202 --> 00:48:11,003
There is no golden rule for everything.

879
00:48:11,723 --> 00:48:14,604
That's what I tried to explain here with the Tai Chi thing.

880
00:48:15,324 --> 00:48:16,705
You need to know what you want to do,

881
00:48:16,785 --> 00:48:19,725
but at the same time be able to adapt every time.

882
00:48:21,446 --> 00:48:21,706
Hey John.

883
00:48:22,969 --> 00:48:27,651
So, you were talking a little bit about the brand strategy and transmedia stuff.

884
00:48:28,151 --> 00:48:31,933
So, one of the more recent decisions that's kind of drawn a little bit of ire from the fans

885
00:48:32,053 --> 00:48:36,575
is taking the Juno plotline, which was started five plus years ago,

886
00:48:37,055 --> 00:48:40,096
and shifting that to the comics and then kind of abandoning it in the games.

887
00:48:40,156 --> 00:48:44,718
And I was wondering if you could talk a little bit about what goes into making a decision like that,

888
00:48:44,738 --> 00:48:46,159
and if there are any lessons learned.

889
00:48:47,793 --> 00:48:51,035
Well, it's always a matter of what's more important.

890
00:48:51,915 --> 00:48:53,936
And who does it affect?

891
00:48:55,436 --> 00:48:57,997
What are the means that need to be put in place

892
00:48:58,057 --> 00:48:59,058
to deliver it properly?

893
00:48:59,718 --> 00:49:02,019
And so it's always discussions.

894
00:49:02,099 --> 00:49:06,541
There is, and so Juno, we know, is really, really,

895
00:49:06,641 --> 00:49:09,842
and was really, really important for a part of our audience.

896
00:49:10,862 --> 00:49:13,023
But when you look at the overall audience,

897
00:49:14,252 --> 00:49:17,015
Not so many people actually know about Juno.

898
00:49:17,555 --> 00:49:21,939
So we knew it was important and we needed a sense of closure for this story.

899
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:29,606
But that was not and that couldn't ever be the core narrative of one big game.

900
00:49:30,767 --> 00:49:35,633
So this is why basically we came up with this solution.

901
00:49:36,073 --> 00:49:39,617
But it's always a discussion, like I tried to explain also

902
00:49:39,657 --> 00:49:42,160
with the discussion we had for features of the game,

903
00:49:42,660 --> 00:49:46,564
there is nothing as, okay, here is the rule on everything

904
00:49:46,625 --> 00:49:47,806
that is valid for everything.

905
00:49:48,186 --> 00:49:48,867
So it's always...

906
00:49:49,993 --> 00:49:51,134
bit by bit, piece by piece.

907
00:49:51,294 --> 00:49:52,834
I don't know how to say that in English properly.

908
00:49:53,534 --> 00:49:55,735
And so at least I think that now there

909
00:49:55,775 --> 00:49:59,276
is a sense of closure for this narrative line.

910
00:50:00,956 --> 00:50:02,657
We know that some people would have preferred

911
00:50:02,697 --> 00:50:03,917
to have that in games.

912
00:50:03,957 --> 00:50:06,698
But at the same time, especially with Origins also,

913
00:50:06,738 --> 00:50:09,999
we knew we wanted to attract and to bring newcomers

914
00:50:10,059 --> 00:50:10,819
to the franchise.

915
00:50:11,499 --> 00:50:15,060
And being set prior to SE1 was a good way to say, you know what?

916
00:50:15,100 --> 00:50:16,680
There is no narrative barrier.

917
00:50:17,341 --> 00:50:18,301
So come with us.

