00:50:34,595 --> 00:50:37,777
Well, we always do surveys, post-launch surveys.

923
00:50:38,257 --> 00:50:41,680
We have teams that are specialized into that,

924
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:46,082
trying to analyze the way people play our games, what they like,

925
00:50:46,122 --> 00:50:47,343
what they dislike about them.

926
00:50:47,883 --> 00:50:51,585
And so this is, I would say, mostly the way

927
00:50:52,186 --> 00:50:54,027
we go into details.

928
00:50:54,427 --> 00:50:56,388
But at the same time, our community managers

929
00:50:56,448 --> 00:50:59,830
are doing a fantastic job to be really in contact.

930
00:51:00,411 --> 00:51:03,573
with the audience in general and so to gather feedbacks,

931
00:51:04,034 --> 00:51:05,775
no matter, I mean, whatever they are,

932
00:51:06,776 --> 00:51:10,079
so that we can try, but there's always a guess in the end,

933
00:51:10,099 --> 00:51:13,022
right, and so, but we also look at the competition,

934
00:51:13,162 --> 00:51:16,865
how the industry is evolving, and so we need to

935
00:51:16,905 --> 00:51:18,566
find our place into that.

936
00:51:18,807 --> 00:51:24,271
There's no massive worldwide, you know, thing to say, okay.

937
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:27,521
and we know exactly what you want.

938
00:51:27,901 --> 00:51:29,662
But we have tools like that, strategies,

939
00:51:29,722 --> 00:51:31,323
to know better, at least.

