00:51:37,326 --> 00:51:38,767
in multiple locations.

944
00:51:39,788 --> 00:51:41,749
Could you give us an idea of how many people

945
00:51:41,809 --> 00:51:44,050
you have in each of the locations,

946
00:51:44,110 --> 00:51:47,852
and is there a limit on how big a geographical location

947
00:51:47,912 --> 00:51:49,573
can be in terms of one part of your team?

948
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:55,521
There's no limits per se, it's really based on each studio management,

949
00:51:56,021 --> 00:51:58,862
you know, to say we're capping for some reason,

950
00:51:59,362 --> 00:52:01,943
this team can't grow more than this.

951
00:52:02,923 --> 00:52:05,184
And then it's really on the producer's side

952
00:52:05,204 --> 00:52:10,605
to be in constant, you know, contact with these teams.

953
00:52:11,345 --> 00:52:15,766
In the end, the last big games are, we're talking about several hundred people.

954
00:52:17,006 --> 00:52:19,607
I can't give you exact figures, but several hundred.

955
00:52:21,456 --> 00:52:23,739
We were, I think, more than 300 in Montreal only.

956
00:52:24,279 --> 00:52:27,624
And so big teams in Singapore, also Sophia,

957
00:52:28,004 --> 00:52:32,009
plus some others in Chengdu, in Montpellier, a lot of studios.

958
00:52:32,029 --> 00:52:35,293
But it's really about collaborating.

959
00:52:35,333 --> 00:52:37,496
So we are, for example, in the lead studio,

960
00:52:38,077 --> 00:52:39,819
typically as a collaboration team.

961
00:52:40,618 --> 00:52:45,720
where we have a producer, a technical guy, a design person.

962
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:50,482
That are the key contact points for the other studios.

963
00:52:51,242 --> 00:52:53,883
And so to make sure that the communication goes well,

964
00:52:54,003 --> 00:52:54,483
it's hard.

965
00:52:54,563 --> 00:52:59,285
It's not always easy, especially for the co-development studios

966
00:52:59,485 --> 00:53:02,267
that are most of the time waiting for things

967
00:53:02,387 --> 00:53:03,047
from the lead studio.

968
00:53:04,211 --> 00:53:06,653
But in the end, it works well.

969
00:53:07,734 --> 00:53:10,457
Does the co-development studio get creative control

